commentary: Mohammad Hafeez to Dhoni, no run that, sir, is a good stop. It would be harsh to call it a drop. It was flighted on off and Dhoni smashed it flat back to the left of the bowler, who stuck his hand out and now he seems to to have done some damage. The physio is out. Sometimes it doesn't help if the reflex takes you towards the ball rather than away from it. It must have stung in this cold. That hit his left-hand thumb

commentary: Mohammed Shami to Saeed Ajmal, OUT and this time he manages to get an edge. It was a similar delivery outside off as the last one, Ajmal tried to run it down to third-man with a horizontal bat and ended up playing at the ball away from his body. The ball takes an edge and it's an easy catch for Dhoni. First wicket for Shami Ahmed in ODIs, 200th catch for Dhoni

commentary: Mohammed Shami to Junaid Khan, OUT he is just run himself out! Although Raina's stop at cover had a fair bit to do with that. Junaid tapped it to the off side and took off immediately, Raina dived and made a half stop. Luckily for him, the ball didn't go to far. He took the ball, realised that there was complete communication breakdown between the batsmen with both on one end, aims and takes down the stumps at striker's end direct. Dhoni was there too had he missed.

But there was no run, but Irfan had run all the way to the other end. The throw came to Ishant's end and he had all the time to collect and run the batsman out. commentary: Sharma to Mohammad Hafeez, OUT caught at midwicket! Hafeez has hit this length ball straight to Yuvraj at midwicket. It wasn't a free-hit as the last ball was no-ball for height. But Pakistan have imploded big time here. Yuvraj runs around the outfield, slides on the field, he gets surrounded by his teammates.
